text: Firecat Blitz and Tempt with Vengence feel like things that win games

I'm personally no longer a fan of Gilded Lotus because at least where I play people will remove it. I'd rather run a rock that'll never get touched than one where I risk someone blowing it up. YMMV there and if nobody touches your Lotus ever then run it.
Draw feels limited. I can see the deck running out of gas.
I still think Ash Barrens is better than either Evolving Wilds or Terramorphic Expanse
Scavenger Grounds is easy grave hate

I guess Blinkmoth Urn and Storm the Vault care about artifact lands. It's some upside but the downside is they eat a dick to Vandalblast, Merciless Eviction, Austere Command, etc. Maybe worth, but not sure.
I don't know I'd run either, but if you're running a basic ETB tapped dual at least Swiftwater Cliffs gains you a life. You're not using guildgate synergy anyway.
Your deck doesn't entirely fall apart without your commander, and maybe nobody steals stuff where you play, but it's enough of a cog that I'd probably want a Homeward Path in there
